CatDescriptText: Mr. M.A. Glick, 211 Forbes Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 19, 1958, pg. 9 with question: "Do you think that a business recession has hit the United States? If so, how has it affected you?" answer reads: "Definitely.  As a partner at the New Diamond Market, I can say that business is down quite a lot.  I would say that the reason is overproduction."
